ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Form used/assessment name
Trial number
session ID/screening ID
VRFCAT Total amount of time spent on assessment
VRFCAT Total amount of time spent on assessment - Unit
VRFCAT Total calculated adjusted time
Notes: Adjusted time is a calculated value which takes the total time it took the subject to complete the assessment and adjusts for time that instructions/error audio was playing and subject couldn't interact with assessment.

ElementDescription: VRFCAT Total calculated adjusted time - Unit
Notes: Adjusted time is a calculated value which takes the total time it took the subject to complete the assessment and adjusts for time that instructions/error audio was playing and subject couldn't interact with assessment.

ElementDescription: VRFCAT Total number of errors in the assessment
VRFCAT Objective/Task
Notes: 1=Read a recipe; 2=Search the pantry at home for ingredients; 3=Make a shopping list for missing ingredients; 4=Pick up a bus schedule; 5=Take the correct bus to the store; 6=Pay the fare in exact change; 7=Locate the items on the shopping list in the store; 8=Pay for the purchases with exact change; 9=Take the correct bus home; 10=Other

ElementDescription: VRFCAT Objective/Task (Other)
VRFCAT Total number of errors during objective/task
VRFCAT Types of errors during objective/task
VRFCAT Total amount of time spent on objective/task
VRFCAT Total amount of time spent on objective/task - Unit
VRFCAT Total calculated adjusted time during objective/task
VRFCAT Total calculated adjusted time during objective/task - Unit
VRFCAT Number of times subject accessed recipe during assessment
VRFCAT Number of times subject accessed bus schedule during assessment
VRFCAT Number of times subject repeated instructions during assessment
VRFCAT Indicate which bus was the correct bus when going to the store
VRFCAT Indicate which bus was the correct bus when going back home
VRFCAT Number of times subject had to revisit aisle 1 (exclude initial visit)
VRFCAT Number of times subject had to revisit aisle 2 (exclude initial visit)
VRFCAT Number of times subject had to revisit aisle 3 (exclude initial visit)
VRFCAT Number of times subject had to revisit aisle 4 (exclude initial visit)
